Some of my favorite photographs and a trailer of my book, Landscapes with Soul. The first edition was sold out, and now, I've received a very limited 150 books of the second edition. Now available through the link on my bio!

This book is a journey through the lens, capturing moments that speak to the soul. Each page tells a story, from the serene winter landscapes of the Nordics to the captivating play of light and shadows. The book includes themes close to my heart, such as Night, Winter, Mood, and Light.

Landscapes With Soul book is a labor of love. Our vision was to create a book that is both incredibly high-quality and environment-friendly—using the highest social and environmental standards on the market.

We aim to make you slow down, get inspired, and experience breathtaking photography and how it is meant to be viewed. This truly is a unique landscape photography book from the north. You can keep it on your table, and it will spark inspiration in you and within anyone who sees it. it.

In between the seasons. Love this short period of time when the cold weather makes unforgettable views and moments. The moment we found this place while travelling through the mist was incredible. These were captured three weeks ago in northern Finland. Enjoy your day! I just ordered a new patch of my photo book Landscapes with Soul. If you are interested let me know!

In the silence of nature. I’ve envisioned this moment for more than six years. Ever since I first saw this scene, I wanted to capture it in a certain way. On this beautiful morning, I finally captured the vista I wanted. A person was watching me through the thick mist and gave the final piece a sense of scale and solitude.
Captured with Nikon Z7 II and Nikkor Z 70-200 f/2.8 S.

These are some of my favorite photographs from the ‘In the Solitude of Nature’ exhibition currently in Redi shopping centre in Helsinki, Finland. 

#nordic #nordichome #decor #prints #nordicstyle #finland #ourfinland #photooftheday

I’m thrilled to welcome you to my new exhibition ’In the Solitude of Nature’ in Helsinki. Location is Finnfoto Gallery in the Redi shopping centre 2nd floor. 

‘In the Solitude of Nature’ is a photography exhibition that showcases Nordic landscapes and atmospheric moments. Capturing unforgettable landscapes from the morning mist to the darkness of night. The images do not just capture places; they capture emotions, bringing you closer to the silence of nature. Featuring 34 of my photographs from the Nordics. 

The exhibition is open from 1.8. to 30.8.2023. Free entry. 

#ourfinland #nordicstyle #photography #nikoncreator

Lost in the moment. A series of my favourite captures from Spain with the Nikon Z 8 and Z lenses. You can now see the video of me and some of my philosophy for photography on @nikoneurope Youtube channel. I was one of nine creators, who embarked on a bus trip from Malaga to Valencia in search of the perfect shot the new Z 8 mirrorless camera.
Packing a host of Z 9 features into a lightweight body, the all-new Z 8 gives image-makers an astounding flexibility to bring our vision to life! 
With its impressive blend of class-leading performance and compact build, this camera is an exciting follow up to the Z 9 and the creative successor to the D850. The Z 8 is a video and stills powerhouse, with key new features such as an in-camera 12-bit RAW for video up to 8.3K/60p or 4.1K/120p, and an array of file sizes and burst speeds for still shooters. 
This is the perfect hybrid camera for creators who want a lighter body for shooting handheld or a full-frame camera that will balance perfectly on any rig, including most gimbals. 
I can't wait for you all to be able to experience this camera and its impressive new features for yourselves!

Take a look at my episode of “THE MOVEMENT” here: https://youtu.be/tRaSji1apW0
